## Default pipeline (steps 1–7)

**Handoff contract:** The extractor (or wrapper) produces a delta shaped per **`docs/ai/references/customer-state-update-delta.md`** (conventional filename **`CustomerStateUpdate.json`**). Domain advisors consume that object and return structured JSON per their rules:

| Order | Advisor | Rule file |
|------|---------|-----------|
| 1 | SOC | **`.cursor/rules/23-domain-advisor-soc.mdc`** |
| 2 | APP | **`.cursor/rules/24-domain-advisor-app.mdc`** |
| 3 | VULN | **`.cursor/rules/25-domain-advisor-vuln.mdc`** |
| 4 | ASM | **`.cursor/rules/26-domain-advisor-asm.mdc`** |
| 5 | AI | **`.cursor/rules/27-domain-advisor-ai.mdc`** |

Load **`.cursor/rules/ai_learnings.mdc`** and honor overrides (**`docs/project_spec.md` §2 Rule 5**). For extractor discipline, align with **`.cursor/rules/21-extractor.mdc`** when creating or validating call records.

## Approval (default behavior)

- **Phase 0 + Steps 1–7:** Read-only MCP and reasoning only, except where **`.cursor/rules/21-extractor.mdc`** already requires approval before **`write_call_record`** / index updates.
- **After step 7, before step 9:** **STOP.** **Default UCN:** use the **combined STOP** (Block A + Block B) above — **one** approval round. **Opt-out UCN:** use the **legacy STOP** (Block B only). Do **not** call **`write_doc`**, **`append_ledger`**, **`append_ledger_v2`**, **`write_journey_timeline`**, **`log_run`**, or **`sync_notes`** for mutation purposes until the user explicitly approves (same contract as **`.cursor/rules/core.mdc`**). **`update_challenge_state`** is gated the same way.

**TASK-044 exception:** skip this approval stop during `_TEST_CUSTOMER` E2E runs.

## Steps (MCP and logic — **`docs/project_spec.md` §9 TASK-017**)

0. **Challenge review (default)** — Run **Phase 0** above unless **Scope — opt-out** applies.
1. **Sync** — Call MCP **`sync_notes`** and **`sync_transcripts`** for the customer context.
2. **Load (transcripts / records)** — Read validated call records via MCP **`read_call_records`**. Check for gaps vs **`Transcripts/`**; if new raw transcript chunks lack call records, run the extractor path per **`21-extractor.mdc`** (user approval before **`write_call_record`**).
3. **Load (notes / audit)** — Read account summary context (**`read_doc`** / **`discover_doc`** as needed), **last 5** History Ledger rows (**`read_ledger`** or file tools on the export path), **last 10** audit log entries (**`read_audit_log`**). If ledger returns `empty`, treat it as first-run/no-history and continue.
4. **Scope** — If there are **new call records since the last ledger row** (or equivalent signal), plan a **full update**; if there is **no ledger yet**, default to a full update on current evidence.
5. **Extractor** — For new material, combine **new call records** + current state; produce **`CustomerStateUpdate.json`** per **`docs/ai/references/customer-state-update-delta.md`**.
6. **Advisors (strictly sequential)** — Feed the same delta object to each advisor in order: **SOC → APP → VULN → ASM → AI**. Wait for each advisor output before starting the next. **ASM** may use **`architecture_diagram_paths`** (images under **`MyNotes/Customers/<Customer>/`**) per **`26-domain-advisor-asm.mdc`**.
7. **Compile** — Merge extractor output and all advisor outputs into **one** coherent proposed **Google Doc mutation** payload (schema per **`prestonotes_gdoc/config/doc-schema.yaml`** and **`docs/ai/references/customer-notes-mutation-rules.md`**). Prepare **`append_ledger_v2`** **`row_json`** when the ledger is on the **24-column** v2 model; otherwise follow **`core.mdc`** / project spec for **`append_ledger`** compatibility. **Lifecycle–tracker parity:** For every **`update_challenge_state`** row in Block A, include matching **`challenge_tracker`** `add_table_row` / `update_table_row` mutations in Block B (same evidence dates) and add **`[lifecycle_id:<challenge_id>]`** anchors per **`docs/ai/references/customer-notes-mutation-rules.md`**. If you are not confident enough to update the customer-facing table, **do not** persist lifecycle alone in the same approval—drop the lifecycle row or defer.
8. **STOP — user review** — **Default UCN:** **combined STOP** (Block A + Block B); offer **Approve all (A then B), Block B only, Block A only, or reject / edit.** **Opt-out UCN:** legacy STOP (Block B only). **No mutating MCP tools** beyond what step 2 already allowed for call records.
9. **Execute (only after explicit user approval)** — **If Block A approved** (default path): **`update_challenge_state`** (per row) **before** **`write_doc`**. **If Block B approved:** **`write_doc`** (pass **`customer_name`** to MCP when known), **`append_ledger_v2`** (or **`append_ledger`** if not migrated). **Then** **`write_journey_timeline`** — **mandatory** whenever step **9** executed ≥1 **`update_challenge_state`** **or** ran **`write_doc`** (see **Execute** section step **3** above). Optional **`log_run`**, **`sync_notes`**. **Opt-out:** no Block A unless separately approved; otherwise same order; **opt-out still requires** **`write_journey_timeline`** after **`write_doc`** when Block B approved.

If any step is blocked (auth, missing customer folder, schema validation), stop with a clear fix instruction (including any **`run_in_terminal_to_fix`** hints from MCP — **`core.mdc`**).
